# CodeMind AI — Day 0 & Day 1 Implementation Plan

## Project Overview

**CodeMind AI** is a browser-based, AI-powered code editor with 5 core features: code generation from natural language, AI-powered autocomplete, bug detection & auto-fix, multi-language support, and a browser-based terminal. The tech stack is **React + Next.js + Monaco Editor** (frontend) and **Node.js + Express** (backend), with **PostgreSQL + Redis** for data, and **Claude/OpenAI API** for AI capabilities.

This plan covers Day 0 (pre-hackathon setup) and Day 1 (project scaffold + core foundation).

---

## 📋 Day 0 — Pre-Hackathon Setup (2–3 Hours)

**Goal**: Zero blockers on Day 1 morning.

### Step 1: Lock MVP Scope

The 5 MVP features (no additions):
1. Code Generation from Natural Language
2. AI-Powered Auto-complete & Suggestions
3. Bug Detection & Auto-fix
4. Multi-Language Support (Python, JS, TS, Java, C++, Go, Rust)
5. Terminal / Run Code in Browser

### Step 2: GitHub Repo & Project Structure

#### [NEW] Project folder structure

```
Galactia_hackathon/
├── backend/
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── config/           # Environment config, constants
│   │   ├── middleware/        # JWT auth, rate limiter, CORS
│   │   ├── routes/            # API route handlers
│   │   ├── services/          # Business logic (AI, execution, user)
│   │   ├── prompts/           # Prompt templates for each AI feature
│   │   ├── models/            # Prisma models / DB interactions
│   │   └── utils/             # Helpers, validators
│   ├── prisma/
│   │   └── schema.prisma      # Database schema
│   ├── server.js              # Express entry point
│   ├── package.json
│   └── .env.example
├── frontend/
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── app/               # Next.js app router pages
│   │   ├── components/        # React components
│   │   │   ├── Editor/        # Monaco Editor wrapper
│   │   │   ├── Sidebar/       # File explorer
│   │   │   ├── Toolbar/       # Top toolbar
│   │   │   ├── AIPanel/       # AI prompt panel
│   │   │   └── Terminal/      # Bottom terminal
│   │   ├── hooks/             # Custom React hooks
│   │   ├── lib/               # API client, utils
│   │   └── styles/            # Global CSS, theme
│   ├── public/
│   ├── package.json
│   └── next.config.js
├── docs/                       # Architecture diagrams, docs
├── .gitignore
├── .env.example
└── README.md
```

### Step 3: Dev Environment Verification

| Check | Command | Expected |
|-------|---------|----------|
| Node.js | `node -v` | v18+ |
| npm | `npm -v` | v9+ |
| Git | `git --version` | Any |
| API Key | Test OpenAI/Claude call | 200 response |

### Step 4: `.env` File Setup

```env
# Backend
PORT=3000
NODE_ENV=development
JWT_SECRET=<generate-random-secret>
OPENAI_API_KEY=<your-key>
# Or use Claude
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=<your-key>
AI_PROVIDER=openai  # or 'anthropic'

# Database
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@localhost:5432/codemind
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379

# Execution
JUDGE0_API_URL=https://judge0-ce.p.rapidapi.com
JUDGE0_API_KEY=<your-key>
```

### Step 5: Product Backlog & Assignments

| Day | Person A (Backend + AI) | Person B (Frontend) |
|-----|------------------------|---------------------|
| 1 | Express server, AI SDK setup, API routes | Next.js + Monaco Editor scaffold |
| 2 | PromptBuilder, code generation endpoint | Editor UI zones, AI panel |
| 3 | Bug detection, auto-fix endpoints | Bug highlights, diff view |
| 4 | Execution engine, terminal API | Terminal panel, dashboard |
| 5 | Testing, demo prep | Polish, video recording |

