### Component 1: Backend Scaffold (Person A)

#### [NEW] [server.js](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Desktop/Galactica/Galactia_hackathon/backend/server.js)
- Express server on port 3000
- CORS enabled for frontend origin
- JSON body parser
- `GET /health` endpoint returning `{ status: 'ok', timestamp }`
- Route mounting for `/api/v1/`

#### [NEW] [package.json](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Desktop/Galactica/Galactia_hackathon/backend/package.json)
- Dependencies: `express`, `cors`, `dotenv`, `jsonwebtoken`, `joi`, `express-rate-limit`
- AI: `openai` (or `@anthropic-ai/sdk`)
- Dev: `nodemon`

#### [NEW] [src/config/index.js](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Desktop/Galactica/Galactia_hackathon/backend/src/config/index.js)
- Load env vars via `dotenv`
- Export config object: port, API keys, DB URLs, rate limits

#### [NEW] [src/middleware/auth.js](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Desktop/Galactica/Galactia_hackathon/backend/src/middleware/auth.js)
- JWT verification middleware (stub for Day 1, full implementation Day 2)

#### [NEW] [src/middleware/rateLimiter.js](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Desktop/Galactica/Galactia_hackathon/backend/src/middleware/rateLimiter.js)
- 10 AI requests/min per user using `express-rate-limit`

#### [NEW] [.env.example](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Desktop/Galactica/Galactia_hackathon/backend/.env.example)
- Template with all required environment variables

